@atumbde As Mayank, this is to compute the actual values during ingestion(realtime) and segment generation (offline). 

How about the combination of the two. We have derivedFieldSpec only to describe the extra json fields (src, transform function, params) but we will also have the derived fields specified in dimensionFieldSpec and MetricFieldSpec and TimeFieldSpec.

@mcvsubbu Note that we haven't decided where to put the extra attributes - schema vs table config.

@kishoreg @mayankshriv : I was confused by the objective then -

> The workaround has been for the users to pre-compute this as part of the input data. This adds additional processing - hadoop job in case of offline and a stream processing job in case of realtime.

If derived columns are materialized columns there is still extra processing on hadoop and streams but it moves the burden from users to Pinot. Is that right ?  (I thought outgoing timefield is computed dynamically based on the spec)
